## Branch Naming

```
<type>/<short-description>
<type>/<ticket-id>-<short-description>
```

| Pattern | Example |
|---------|---------|
| Feature | `feat/user-avatar-upload` |
| Bug fix | `fix/login-redirect-loop` |
| With ticket | `feat/AUTH-142-email-verification` |
| Release | `release/2.4.0` |
| Hotfix | `hotfix/null-pointer-checkout` |

- Use **kebab-case** only; no spaces, no uppercase
- Keep branch names **short and descriptive** (≤ 50 chars)
- Delete branches after merging

---

## Commits Best Practices

- **One logical change per commit** — if you need "and" to describe it, split it
- Commit **working code** — never commit broken builds or failing tests to shared branches
- Don't commit generated files, build artefacts, or `node_modules`
- Use `git add -p` (patch mode) to stage only the relevant hunks when a file has mixed changes
- Amend or rebase to clean up **before** pushing — squash WIP / typo commits
- Sign commits with GPG (`git config commit.gpgsign true`) in security-sensitive repos

